file-contents:
  releasenotes/notes/change-ipa-version-cacaec52a55188cc.yaml:
    features: ['By adding extra variable ``-e ipa_upstream_release=stable-mitaka``
        for instance,

        the deployment can now use all ramdisk and kernel images available in

        https://tarballs.openstack.org/ironic-python-agent/tinyipa/files/

        instead of the default ``master``.


        Furthermore, as some of these files do not have any .sha256

        checksum associated to them, the downloading of these file

        is now just issuing a "warning" and is not reported as an

        Ansible error in the final summary.

        ']
  releasenotes/notes/custom-partitioning-78d7ac12d80a993f.yaml:
    features: ["Custom partitioning YAML file can now be specified using partitioning_file\n\
        variable which contains a path to the YAML file describing the partitions\n\
        layout. For example:\n\n.. code-block:: yaml\n\n    - local_loop:\n      \
        \  name: image0\n    - partitioning:\n        base: image0\n        label:\
        \ mbr\n        partitions:\n          - name: root\n            flags: [ boot,primary\
        \ ]\n            size: 6G\n            mkfs:\n              type: xfs\n  \
        \            label: \"img-rootfs\"\n              mount:\n               \
        \ mount_point: /\n                fstab:\n                  options: \"rw,relatime\"\
        \n                  fck-passno: 1\n          - name: tmp\n            size:\
        \ 1G\n            mkfs:\n              type: xfs\n              mount:\n \
        \               mount_point: /tmp\n                fstab:\n              \
        \      options: \"rw,nosuid,nodev,noexec,relatime\"\n          - name: var\n\
        \            size: 7G\n            mkfs:\n              type: xfs\n      \
        \        mount:\n                mount_point: /var\n                fstab:\n\
        \                  options: \"rw,relatime\"\n          - name: log\n     \
        \       size: 5G\n            mkfs:\n              type: xfs\n           \
        \   mount:\n                mount_point: /var/log\n                fstab:\n\
        \                  options: \"rw,relatime\"\n          - name: home\n    \
        \        size: 1G\n            mkfs:\n              type: xfs\n          \
        \    mount:\n                mount_point: /home\n                fstab:\n\
        \                  options: \"rw,nodev,relatime\"\n\n\nFor more informations\
        \ please refer to the following links:\n`Disk Image Layout Section <https://docs.openstack.org/diskimage-builder/latest/user_guide/building_an_image.html#disk-image-layout>`_\n\
        `Standard Partitioning <http://teknoarticles.blogspot.fr/2017/07/build-and-use-security-hardened-images.html>`_\n\
        `LVM Partitioning <http://teknoarticles.blogspot.fr/2017/11/security-hardened-images-with-volumes.html>`_\n"]
  releasenotes/notes/no-classic-drivers-0b8a346bcab8a004.yaml:
    upgrade: ['The deprecated support for classic drivers has been removed.

        ']
  releasenotes/notes/populate_ntp_servers_dnsmasq-249d2a26b94b0bf1.yaml:
    features: ['Allow to populate the NTP servers setting of dnsmasq. This is optional,
        but if ``dnsmasq_ntp_servers``setting is set, it adds a ``dhcp-option=42,dnsmasq_ntp_servers``
        to the generated dnsmasq configuration for bifrost.']
    other: ['When configuring the ``dnsmasq_ntp_servers`` setting, several NTP servers
        can be specified, separated by commas.']
  releasenotes/notes/store-introspection-data-bc4f2fef2f5bb543.yaml:
    features: ['Stores introspection data in nginx.


        In the absence of swift, we can now use the bifrost nginx web server -

        masquerading as an object store - to store raw and processed introspection

        data for nodes.  This is configured via the boolean variable

        ``inspector_store_data_in_nginx`` and is enabled by default.

        ']
